## APPLICATION CONTEXT
- **App**: Thinkboard — MERN Notes Application
- **Backend**: Node.js / Express 5 / Mongoose 9 (ES Modules)
- **Frontend**: React / Vite / Tailwind CSS
- **Testing**: Jest 30 + Supertest 7 + ESLint 10
- **Repo**: github.com/Flirnz/mern-thinkboard

## 11-STAGE PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE
1. **SCM** — GitHub (branching, webhooks, commit structure)
2. **Orchestration** — Jenkins CI on AWS EC2
3. **Build & Test** — npm install, ESLint, Jest/Supertest (with coverage XML/LCOV), and E2E Tests (min 3 cases)
4. **SAST** — SonarQube quality gates (importing coverage & test reports)
5. **SCA** — Trivy filesystem scan (pre-container)
6. **Containerization** — Docker (multi-stage builds, layer optimization)
7. **Container Scan** — Trivy image scan
8. **Artifact Registry** — AWS ECR or Docker Hub
9. **CD Engine** — ArgoCD & Helm (GitOps reconciliation)
10. **Orchestration Target** — AWS EKS (Kubernetes)
11. **Observability** — Prometheus + Grafana

## IMPORTANT DEVIATION FROM ORIGINAL SPEC
The original anchor specifies Maven for Stage 3 (Build & Compile). This project is JavaScript/Node.js — NOT Java. Stage 3 uses `npm install`, `npm run lint`, and `npm test` instead of Maven. All other stages remain aligned with the original architecture.

